  "prompt": "When and how did Gautama Buddha die?",
  "response": "Gautama Buddha, the founder of Buddhism, is traditionally believed to have died in around 483 BCE. His death is referred to as the Parinirvana, which means the final passing away. According to Buddhist tradition, Buddha passed away at the age of 80 in a grove of sal trees in Kushinagar, which is in present-day Uttar Pradesh, India.\n\nThe cause of Buddha's death is a subject of different interpretations. According to some accounts, he died from food poisoning after eating a meal offered by a blacksmith named Cunda. Alternatively, some suggest that the meal may have been something that upset his already fragile health rather than a case of deliberate poisoning. After falling seriously ill, Buddha reportedly spent his final moments giving instructions to his disciples and entered a deep meditative state before passing away peacefully.",
